The paper focuses on the problem of semantic code repair, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture for scoring repair candidates, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses rule-based processors to generate repair candidates, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also uses a large corpus of real-world source code, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on developing a robust contextual repair model could also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
